to the superfine consistancy of powdered sugar or better. This is a must! If not done so, your completed rocket WILL NOT FUNCTION PROPERLY! Charcoal being used should be of willow dust on the smaller rockets and a mixture of willow dust and coarse mesh sizes (40-100m) combined, (The latter being lessor), for larger ones. The ratio of charcoal is approximately 50% dust - 50% coarse on 8 oz. size, and 30% dust to 70% coarse on 1 lb and larger sizes (again this must be adjusted properly to suit your needs). The coarse mesh charcoal also adds a spark "tail" to the rocket upon ascending. If your rocket explodes before or during ascending, add more charcoal to the fuel. If it ascends too slowly, add less charcoal. Thus you can pinpoint a particular mixture just right for your particular requirements.       DOWNLOADED FROM P-80 SYSTEMS                                ␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀␀